'''Fotoform''' was a group founded in 1949 by the photographer [[Otto Steinert]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artechock.de/kunst/magazin/be/toschn.htm|title=besprechung fotoform und toni schneider}} (in German)</ref> Until 1958 it was the preeminent group of avant-garde West German photographers. Other collaborators were [[Peter Keetman]], [[Ludwig Windstoßer]], [[Toni Schneiders]], [[Wolfgang Reisewitz]], [[Siegfried Lauterwasser]], [[Heinz Hajek-Halke]] and Christer Christian (the pseudonym of the Swedish photographer [[Christer Strömholm]]).

It made photographic experiments and sought to draw attention to the creative possibilities of photography which had been extingished by [[Art of the Third Reich|Nazi cultural policy]].

