'''Mezzoramia''' is a mythical paradise in the African desert, from a story by [[Simon Berington]]. Gaudentio di Lucca, the main character of the tale, discovers the secret, narrow road that provides the only access to the oasis, and resides there for twenty-five years.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0HLzAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA104&lpg=PA104&dq=mezzoramia&source=bl&ots=lTS0X2AW8n&sig=9dvWNuIBW22NwEzil327DwGuGik&hl=en&sa=X&ei=a5WoVICnH4HSoATbmAI&ved=0CEAQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=mezzoramia&f=false |title=Encyclopedia of Imaginary and Mythical Places |first=Theresa |last=Bane |publisher=[[McFarland Publishing]] |page=104 |date=March 7, 2014 |accessdate=January 4, 2015 |isbn=978-0786478484}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=The History of Fiction |year=1814|first=John |last=Dunlop |authorlink=John Colin Dunlop}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=[[Brewer's Dictionary of Phrase and Fable]] |editor=[[E. Cobham Brewer]] |year=1870}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Reader's Handbook: Famous Names in Fiction, Allusions, References, Proverbs, Plots, Stories and Poems |editor=E. Cobham Brewer|publisher=Gale Group|date=June 1966 |pages=408, 702 |isbn=978-0810301535}}</ref>
